Text.Value: I've got bigger problems!
Be a goodly sinner, and dash off to kill her posthaste... If you don't, I worry greatly for your future.
I've been running hither and thither trying to speak with you again! But Master does rather shuffle about a lot. An old Butler's knees can't keep up.
Oh dear, oh dear.
Fine, I'll do it.
We shouldn't let you get too distracted. Make sure you kill her afterwards. And soon.
Where is she?
Peasants love grovelling afore those of good breeding. The shameful poor Isobel protects want to die by your royal hand.
You must have killed me hundreds of times since you were a youngling. I hope there will be hundreds more...
You've employed some skilled servants, my Liege! You murdered me very well! I cannot wait to see you unleash your minions upon the tower.
It will be easy. Her protectors have left. She thinks she can defend herself. She cannot, not against you.
This isn't me. I am not what I used to be.
What will happen, if I don't do it?
The Moonmaiden Isobel... she is all but alone now... I have been watching her.
This is simply a matter of royal principle. We hear of a darling thing shining a light in the darkness? We kill her!
Have you forgotten? Whenever this frail carcass perishes, you shall always be sent a fresh Sceleritas.
Didn't you die?
I'm never obeying you. Do you hear me? Never!
But hovel or not - there is exquisite killing to be had there. Efficient killing!
Apologies for my tardiness. I'll get right to it.
If you spite your loving Butler now, I shall be forced to report back home that you have been naughty.
You think Lord Ketheric is the worst foe you could face?
Please, my Liege. Do not disappoint your Father... Kill the cleric at once - or else.
Why do you want me to kill her?
I am not certain. You were never disobedient before your little accident.
What has come over you? You cut such a dapper figure, slashing apart the Grove...
Attack.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Leads to the same combat state as if you attacked him at the Bhaal Temple MainDoor scene - he doesn't resist and gets the 'happy' state

Text.Value: I'm not doing anything unless you reveal my past.
You may kill in your sleep again. You may be executed. You might even be disinherited.
This tower will still be here for you to bombard when you return.
Oh my!
Proof is required you are worthy of the inheritance you are very close to receiving.
Oh, precious Liege. Look at you! All grown up and storming such a large tower! And with such wanton force!
Now is the perfect time to finally kill you.
I just want to be left alone. I'm not doing this.
I don't want to harm her. I will save this cursed land.
You murdered me very well! And look at you! About to storm a whole tower!
Oh! Do! Do! If this frail carcass ever perishes, you will always be sent a fresh Butler.
I'll go to her with knives.
The Inn of Last Light. I can understand why you did not linger there. 'Tis rather a hovel.
It will come soon. Very soon. But we must impress our betters before you can be trusted with your old station...
*In the depths of your liver, the bile salt bubbles, as if letting out a knowing chuckle.*
Let's not find out.
A perfect crime awaits. You must go and kill this target, and you will be rewarded dearly.
I have already indulged in one death here... but one more never hurts!
Don't mistake me, Master, I want you to kill everyone.
It is rather loathly of Sceleritas to disrupt your romp, but I cannot allow the Master to forget duty, and keep carousing like this.
If you do not, it will be terribly embarrassing for the both of us.
The Urge, Master... Fear the Urge.
I did! It felt wonderful.

Synopsis: The player has never spoken to Isobel before starting the assault on Moonrise. The Butler appears in front of the player on the bridge to Moonrise to remind the Dark Urge player that they must kill Isobel if they want to please Bhaal.
